# CODEOWNERS — governance for the Universal .claude AI Project OS
#
# This maps review ownership across the .claude/ families so security-, safety-, and
# constitution-level changes get the right eyes before merge (GitHub docs:
# https://docs.github.com/articles/about-code-owners).
#
# IMPORTANT — this ships with placeholder handles. Replace every @your-org/... team
# below with real GitHub users/teams for your organization before this file takes
# effect. GitHub silently ignores rules that point at a team/user with no repo access —
# it will not error the build, it will simply skip requesting that review. Last rule
# to match a path wins, so more specific paths should stay below broader ones.
#
# This file lives in .github/ (not .claude/) because CODEOWNERS is a GitHub review
# mechanism, not part of the portable .claude/ tree — it does not travel with a copy
# of .claude/ into another repo and does not need to.

# ── Default owner for anything not matched below ────────────────────────────
*                                               @your-org/maintainers

# ── The constitution — changes here affect every project this template is
#    copied into; require the highest bar of review ─────────────────────────
/.claude/CLAUDE.md                             @your-org/maintainers @your-org/staff-eng

# ── Always-on safety baseline — tightening or loosening the deny/ask lists,
#    or adding/editing a hook, requires security sign-off ───────────────────
/.claude/settings.json                         @your-org/security-team
/.claude/hooks/                                @your-org/security-team
/.claude/docs/HOOKS_SAFETY_MODEL.md            @your-org/security-team

# ── Security- and privacy-sensitive agents, checklists, and docs ────────────
/.claude/agents/quality/security-auditor.md            @your-org/security-team
/.claude/agents/quality/privacy-compliance-auditor.md  @your-org/security-team @your-org/legal
/.claude/agents/quality/production-readiness-auditor.md @your-org/security-team
/.claude/checklists/security.md                @your-org/security-team
/.claude/checklists/privacy-compliance.md      @your-org/security-team @your-org/legal
/.claude/checklists/dependencies.md            @your-org/security-team
/.claude/templates/threat-model.md             @your-org/security-team
/.claude/templates/security-model.md           @your-org/security-team
/.claude/docs/COMPLIANCE.md                    @your-org/security-team @your-org/legal
/SECURITY.md                                   @your-org/security-team

# ── Orchestrator and routing — changes affect delegation and team assembly
#    across every project type, not just one ────────────────────────────────
/.claude/agents/core/orchestrator.md           @your-org/staff-eng
/.claude/orchestration/                        @your-org/staff-eng
/.claude/docs/ORG_CONFIG_LAYERING.md           @your-org/staff-eng

# ── Trust-spine toolchain and CI — the deterministic gates everything else
#    is checked against ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
/.claude/scripts/                              @your-org/staff-eng
/.github/workflows/                            @your-org/staff-eng

# ── Governance meta — who can change how contributions/review/process work ──
/CONTRIBUTING.md                               @your-org/maintainers
/.github/CODEOWNERS                            @your-org/maintainers
/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md                            @your-org/maintainers
/.claude/templates/rfc.md                      @your-org/maintainers
/docs/rfcs/                                    @your-org/maintainers @your-org/staff-eng
